A '''duel''' between two [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force users]] occurred on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Terephon]] in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], being the fifth and final confrontation between [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Lumiya]], [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lady of the Sith]]. It occurred during the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], when Skywalker blamed Lumiya for the [[Skirmish on Kavan|death]] of his [[Marriage/Legends|wife]] [[Mara Jade Skywalker]] and wanted revenge, resulting in Lumiya's [[Death/Legends|death]].

==Prelude==
{{Quote|My work and my life are done, Jacen. I'd really welcome a rest.|Lumiya|<ref name="Sac" />}}
Having ensured that her pupil, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]], had fulfilled his destiny in becoming a [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] with the [[Skirmish on Kavan|murder]] of his aunt, [[Mara Jade Skywalker]], Lumiya accepted that her life's work was complete, and after a short discussion with Solo on the Sith world of [[Ziost/Legends|Ziost]], set off to [[Terephon]], near [[Kavan]], where Jade Skywalker had met her end. Luke Skywalker, following a call in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] urging him to [[Terephon]], traveled grief-stricken to the [[Transitory Mists]] and awaited his quarry. He had no doubt that Lumiya had killed his wife, unaware as he was of the facts surrounding Mara's death. As the remainder of the Skywalker and Solo clan, minus Jacen, grieved on [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]], Lumiya emerged in the [[Terephon system/Legends|Terephon system]].

==Dogfight over Terephon==
{{Quote|You know any one of us would gladly do it for you.|[[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]] offering help to Luke, shortly before Lumiya's arrival|<ref name="Sac" />}}
Demonstrating his superior piloting skills in his [[StealthX]], Skywalker soon forced Lumiya down onto the surface of Terephon. The old rivals, once lovers themselves, landed their respective ships on a mesa overlooking a grand Terephonian city. Skywalker leapt from his vessel, clutching [[Luke Skywalker's green lightsaber/Legends|his]] [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] in a two-handed grip, forgoing [[Luke Skywalker's shoto|the]] [[Shoto lightsaber/Legends|shoto]] he had previously used to combat Lumiya's [[Lumiya's lightwhip|signature weapon]], the [[Lightwhip/Legends|lightwhip]].

==The duel==
As the two opponents met in battle, it soon became apparent that the duel was in Skywalker's favor. Although the Dark Lady fought as best she could, there were no distractions to deter the inexorable might of the Grand Master; unlike [[Duel on Roqoo Depot|Roqoo]] or the resort station at [[Gilatter VIII]], Lumiya was not surrounded by objects or hostages. Atop the cliff, Skywalker ducked inside her defenses and their weapons clashed. Slowly, the Jedi forced Lumiya to the edge of the mesa by continually beating down her guard, each step eroding her strength and sending her feet sliding towards the sheer drop. The ground began to crumble, and Lumiya slipped, her lightwhip tumbling off the precipice. As the Dark Lady fell, Skywalker grabbed her by the wrist and raised her back onto firm ground, meeting her intense gaze. With a long arc of his lightsaber, he brought the blade around to decapitate his opponent of so many years.

==Aftermath==
When [[Ben Skywalker|Ben]] revealed it could not have been Lumiya who murdered his wife, Luke sank into deep despair, unable to live with the fact that he had killed the wrong person. He grew to believe that it had been the rogue [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Alema Rar]], and organized a task force to hunt the deranged [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] down. It would be time before he learned that Jacen Solo, now the new Dark Lord, was the true culprit.

